<h1>FitMind: Exercise & Stress Tracker - Required Languages and Technologies</h1>

<h2>1. Frontend (User Interface)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>HTML</strong>: For structuring the content and layout of the website.</li>
  <li><strong>CSS</strong>: For styling and designing the layout, making the website visually appealing and user-friendly.</li>
  <li><strong>JavaScript</strong>: For interactivity, such as handling user inputs, updating content dynamically, and managing form submissions.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Backend (Data Processing and Storage)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Node.js</strong> (JavaScript) or <strong>Python</strong> (with frameworks like Flask or Django): For building the server-side functionality, managing routes, and processing data.</li>
  <li><strong>Database</strong> (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB): To store user data, including stress levels, exercise logs, and any other user information.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Optional Frameworks and Libraries</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Frontend Libraries</strong>:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>React</strong> or <strong>Vue.js</strong> (JavaScript libraries): For building a more dynamic and responsive user interface.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>CSS Frameworks</strong>:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Bootstrap</strong> or <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong>: To speed up and simplify styling.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Additional Technologies</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>APIs</strong>: For integrating any external data (e.g., stress management tips, exercise recommendations).</li>
  <li><strong>Authentication</strong>: Libraries like <strong>Auth0</strong> or <strong>Firebase</strong> for secure user login and authentication.</li>
</ul>
